%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20parents%20are%20struggling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20stranded%20parents.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557698336d588dc55d22e4b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMillennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20parents%20are%20finding%20themselves%20isolated%2C%20overwhelmed%2C%20and%20stressed%20out%20about%20money.%3Cp%3EEleanor%20Davis%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKyle%20Taylor%20doesn't%20have%20a%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alabama-based%2026-year-old%20and%20his%20girlfriend%20were%20delighted%20when%20their%20daughter%20was%20born%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20but%20nowadays%20they%20are%20feeling%20a%20bit%20lost.%20To%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%20Taylor%20has%20been%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20at%20work.%20And%20while%20his%20girlfriend%20stays%20at%20home%2C%20Taylor's%20schedule%20and%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20baby%20have%20left%20them%20stretched%20thin.%20But%20none%20of%20Taylor's%20friends%20are%20parents%2C%20and%20most%20don't%20plan%20on%20having%20kids%2C%20leaving%20them%20unsure%20how%20to%20chip%20in%20with%20a%20newborn.%20Growing%20up%2C%20Taylor%20always%20heard%20about%20the%20proverbial%20village%20it%20takes%20to%20raise%20a%20child.%20Now%20that%20he%20actually%20has%20one%2C%20he%20realizes%20there%20is%20no%20village%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20already%20this%20kind%20of%20disconnect%20for%20us.%20People%20aren't%20thinking%20in%20terms%20of%20like%2C%20how%20can%20I%20support%20my%20friend%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRather%2C%20I%20think%20they're%20just%20kind%20of%20grateful%20that%20they're%20not%20in%20my%20situation%20of%20having%20someone%20to%20care%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20parents%20are%20finding%20themselves%20isolated.%20Maybe%20they've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fday-care-costs-us-mom-paid-over-22000-for-childcare-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20away%20from%20their%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20search%20of%20a%20well-paying%20job%20or%20cheaper%20rent.%20When%20parents%20are%20close%20by%2C%20they're%20often%20still%20working%20and%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20pitch%20in%20with%20childcare.%20Outside%20the%20family%20tree%2C%20many%20of%20their%20peers%20either%20can't%20afford%20or%20are%20choosing%20not%20to%20have%20kids%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20understand%20what%20their%20new-parent%20friends%20are%20dealing%20with.%20And%20raising%20children%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20expensive%2C%20adding%20an%20economic%20weight%20to%20their%20worries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20left%20with%20kind%20of%20a%20wreckage%20of%20an%20economy%20here%20in%20the%20states.%20It's%20tough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%2C%20really%20tough%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%20like%20most%20people%2C%20and%20not%20really%20getting%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20support%20or%20feeling%20like%20people%20my%20age%20really%20understand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20paradigm%20of%20parenthood%20is%20made%20up%20of%20a%20series%20of%20impossible%20decisions%3A%20leaving%20jobs%2C%20moving%20away%20from%20friends%20or%20families%2C%20or%20working%20longer%20hours%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20Natalie%20Groff%2C%20a%2033-year-old%20mother%20of%20four%2C%20summed%20up%20her%20cohort's%20dilemma%20succinctly%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20things%20are%20right%20now%2C%20it's%20pretty%20messed%20up%20and%20the%20odds%20are%20definitely%20stacked%20against%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20cost%20for%20(pa)rents%20is%20too%20damn%20high%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20have%20spent%20the%20past%20two%20decades%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-financial-futures-jobs-economy-money-pandemic-recession-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrying%20to%20find%20their%20economic%20footing%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20two%20recessions%2C%20a%20college-debt%20crisis%2C%20a%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20worst%20labor%20market%20in%20a%20half-century%20didn't%20make%20it%20easy.%20But%20they%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20behind%20them%20have%20finally%20caught%20up%20to%20previous%20generations%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20income%2C%20Jean%20Twenge%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.simonandschuster.com%2Fbooks%2FGenerations%2FJean-M-Twenge%2F9781982181611%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenerations%3A%20The%20Real%20Differences%20Between%20Gen%20Z%2C%20Millennials%2C%20Gen%20X%2C%20Boomers%2C%20and%20Silents%E2%80%94and%20What%20They%20Mean%20for%20America's%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20median%20incomes%20for%20younger%20adults%20are%20at%20all-time%20highs%2C%20even%20when%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Twenge%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20partially%20because%20more%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20went%20to%20college%20and%20got%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20and%20folks%20who%20get%20those%20degrees%20make%20more%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20their%20incomes%20have%20climbed%2C%20the%20price%20of%20all%20kinds%20of%20child-rearing%20essentials%20has%20skyrocketed%20even%20higher.%20The%20cost%20of%20childcare%20has%20tripled%20since%201991%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%20and%20research%20by%20economists%20at%20Bank%20of%20America%20found%20that%20the%20average%20family%20was%20spending%20over%20%24700%20a%20month%20on%20care%20as%20of%20September%2C%20a%20figure%2032%25%20higher%20than%20in%202019.%20Even%20as%20childcare%20workers%20grapple%20with%20low%20pay%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-workers-quitting-low-pay-childcare-shortage-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etough%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20report%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20found%20that%20the%20precarious%20system%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fproviders-struggle-to-keep-funding-rising-childcare-costs-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderfunded%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20relies%20on%20%26quot%3Boverburdened%20families%20and%20underpaid%20childcare%20workers%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20meant%20that%20childcare%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-is-unaffordable-almost-everywhere-in-america-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunaffordable%20almost%20everywhere%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChildcare%20prices%20are%20untenable%20for%20families%20across%20all%20care%20types%2C%20age%20groups%2C%20and%20county%20population%20sizes%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%2C%20released%20in%20January%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F8c2cZ%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Change%20in%20daycare%20prices%20over%20time%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EChildcare%20isn't%20even%20the%20start%20of%20increasingly%20expensive%20child-rearing%20expenses.%20Since%201997%2C%20the%20price%20of%20baby%20food%20and%20formula%20has%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbeta.bls.gov%2FdataViewer%2Fview%2Ftimeseries%2FCUUR0000SEFT05%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoubled%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wbur.org%2Fnews%2F2022%2F06%2F01%2Fdiaper-banks-inflation-parents-babies-expensive%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENielsenIQ%3C%2Fa%3E%20data%20showing%20the%20price%20of%20diapers%20rising%20by%20almost%2022%25%20from%202018%20to%202022%20alone.%20As%20fast%20as%20the%20money%20comes%20in%20from%20the%20pay%20raises%20that%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20secured%2C%20for%20parents%20the%20money%20goes%20right%20back%20out.%20That%20may%20explain%20why%20the%20younger%20generations%20are%20falling%20behind%20on%20their%20debt%20payments.%20America's%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20are%20seeing%20about%20twice%20as%20much%20debt%20going%20into%20serious%20delinquency%20compared%20with%20those%20ages%2050%20to%2059%20and%2060%20to%2069.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FY90TC%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Debt%20transitioning%20into%20serious%20delinquency%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20realities%20can%20force%20many%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20parents%20to%20make%20tough%20choices.%20Most%20of%20the%20income%20gains%20made%20by%20young%20people%2C%20Twenge%20said%2C%20have%20come%20from%20women's%20salaries.%20More%20women%20are%20graduating%20from%20college%20and%20seeing%20their%20incomes%20start%20to%20catch%20up.%20But%20that%20can%20be%20a%20double-edged%20sword%20for%20young%20heterosexual%20couples%3A%20It%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20forgo%20either%20parent's%20high%20salary%2C%20so%20they%20have%20to%20wrangle%20incredibly%20expensive%20childcare%20instead.%20A%20family%20in%20New%20York%20City%20with%20just%20one%20young%20child%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-daycare-cost-new-york-city-crisis-housing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20have%20to%20make%20%24300%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20childcare%20costs%20to%20meet%20federal%20affordability%20standards.%20And%20the%20longer-term%20boom%20in%20women's%20career%20opportunities%20means%20the%20mothers%20and%20grandmothers%20who%20might%20have%20previously%20been%20available%20to%20pitch%20in%20care%20are%20no%20longer%20available%2C%20because%20they're%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Groff%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20four%3A%20When%20her%20old%20workplace%20shuttered%2C%20she%20became%20a%20stay-at-home%20parent%20again%2C%20which%20alleviated%20the%20cost%20of%20after-school%20care.%20The%20savings%20were%20so%20significant%20that%20when%20a%20supervisor%20job%20opportunity%20came%20up%2C%20the%20salary%20wouldn't%20be%20enough%20to%20break%20even%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20childcare.%20So%20she's%20once%20again%20working%20as%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20while%20studying%20for%20a%20master's%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20ways%2C%20it%20was%20very%20comforting%20to%20come%20back%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20other%20ways%20it's%20just%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20I%20know%20this%20is%20what%20I%20can%20do%20for%20my%20family%20at%20this%20time%2C%20but%20I%20almost%20have%20this%20master's%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20am%20I%20going%20to%20use%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Jimmy%20Gomez%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20California%20who%20helped%20found%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdads-caucus-house-democrats-childcare-parental-leave-child-tax-credit-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECongressional%20Dads%20Caucus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20knows%20these%20struggles%20personally.%20Gomez%20is%20the%20father%20of%20a%2013-month-old%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeople.com%2Fparents%2Fcongressman-jimmy-gomez-baby-carrier-house-speaker-vote%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebriefly%20went%20viral%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%20after%20being%20pictured%20strapped%20onto%20his%20father's%20chest%20during%20the%20first%20chaotic%20round%20of%20House%20Speaker%20votes.%20Gomez%20told%20me%20that%20what%20we're%20seeing%20right%20now%20%26quot%3Bis%20just%20a%20ton%20of%20pressure%20on%20parents%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20making%20ends%20meet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20not%20exempt%20from%20that%20pressure%20%E2%80%94%20his%20family%20is%20paying%20nearly%20%242%2C700%20a%20month%20for%20just%20three%20days%20of%20childcare%20a%20week.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Gomez%20added%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F01%2F25%2Frealestate%2Frent-burdened-american-households.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20American%20family%20that%20rents%20their%20home%20is%20now%20considered%20rent-burdened%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20they%20spend%20at%20least%2030%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20housing.%20Between%20childcare%20and%20rent%2C%20two%20major%20expenses%20can%20easily%20eat%20up%20over%20half%20of%20a%20family's%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20means%20less%20money%20for%20a%20401(k)%2C%20savings%2C%20college%2C%20starting%20a%20small%20business%2C%20repairs%20to%20your%20house.%20Just%20the%20basic%20stuff%20becomes%20more%20and%20more%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20stress%20is%20real%2C%20especially%20for%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%2C%20the%20Gen%20Z%20parent%2C%20said%20he%20understood%20this%20problem%20deeply.%20After%20the%20birth%20of%20his%20daughter%2C%20his%20job%20and%20salary%20didn't%20really%20change%2C%20but%20his%20expenses%20did.%20He%20says%20his%20family%20is%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%20and%20just%20%26quot%3Bhemorrhaging%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20fairly%20decent%20job.%20It%20would%20be%20good%20for%20a%20single%20person%20with%20no%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20no%20disposable%20income%2C%20basically%2C%20between%20rent%20and%20groceries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20loss%20of%20a%20village%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20financial%20pressures%20of%20modern%20parenting%2C%20there%20is%20also%20another%20fundamental%20problem%3A%20isolation.%20The%20kinds%20of%20places%20that%20encouraged%20community%20and%20allowed%20young%20parents%20to%20meet%20one%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-blame-loneliness-on-housing-affordability-crisis-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20disappearing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20as%20suburbs%20%E2%80%94%20renowned%20for%20their%20sprawl%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-leaving-cities-for-suburbs-amid-pandemic-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esee%20more%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20moving%20in%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20even%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Byoung%20parent%26quot%3B%20is%20changing%3A%20In%201990%2C%20the%20median%20mother%20in%20the%20US%20had%20her%20first%20child%20at%20age%2027%3B%20as%20of%202019%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fstories%2F2022%2F04%2Ffertility-rates-declined-for-younger-women-increased-for-older-women.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThese%2520changing%2520fertility%2520rates%2520by%2Cto%252028%2520years%2520old%252C%2520respectively.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20age%20had%20risen%20to%2030%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20look%20at%20one%20proxy%20for%20a%20lost%20village%3A%20how%20often%20kids%20are%20walking%20to%20school.%20It's%20become%20a%20familiar%20joking%20refrain%20that%2C%20back%20in%20the%20day%2C%20everyone%20would%20make%20their%20hikes%20to%20school.%20But%20there's%20truth%20to%20that.%20The%20share%20of%20kids%20usually%20walking%20and%20biking%20to%20school%20has%20fallen%20%E2%80%94%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthworkscollective.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F07%2FNHTS_school_travel_report_2011_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E48%25%20in%201969%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnhts.ornl.gov%2Fassets%2FFHWA_NHTS_%2520Brief_Traveltoschool_032519.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E10%25%20in%202017%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202017%2C%20about%2054%25%20of%20kids%20were%20traveling%20to%20school%20in%20private%20vehicles%2C%20with%20bus%20transport%20coming%20in%20at%20a%20distant%20second%20at%2033.2%25.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20over%20half%20of%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchildcaredeserts.org%2F2018%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elived%20in%20childcare%20deserts%20as%20of%202018%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20areas%20where%20the%20number%20of%20children%20outnumbered%20licensed%20care%20slots%20by%20at%20least%20three%20to%20one%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20parents%20have%20to%20go%20farther%2C%20or%20pay%20more%2C%20or%20stay%20home%20to%20access%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20as%20of%202018%2C%20just%2016%25%20of%20Americans%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2018%2F05%2F22%2Fwhat-unites-and-divides-urban-suburban-and-rural-communities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20reported%20feeling%20very%20attached%20to%20their%20communities.%20Younger%20Americans%20seemed%20particularly%20detached%2C%20with%20just%208%25%20of%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20saying%20they%20were%20very%20attached%20to%20their%20local%20community%2C%20and%2013%25%20of%20those%20ages%2030%20to%2049%20saying%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20increasing%20sense%20of%20isolation%20is%20seeping%20across%20society%20even%20though%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20want%20to%20be%20near%20one%20another%20and%20the%20things%20that%20they%20enjoy.%20An%20April%20survey%20of%202%2C000%20urban%20adults%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Freports%2Fnar-community-and-transportation-preferences-surveys%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Association%20of%20Realtors%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20nearly%20half%20of%20millennials%20said%20they%20considered%20living%20in%20a%20walkable%20community%20to%20be%20very%20important%2C%20with%20both%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20saying%20they'd%20rather%20live%20closer%20to%20public%20transit%20than%20a%20highway.%20Millennials%20with%20kids%20said%20they'd%20happily%20trade%20a%20smaller%20yard%20for%20a%20walkable%20community%2C%20and%20both%20cohorts%20said%20they'd%20pay%20more%20to%20live%20in%20a%20walkable%20community.%20But%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20young%20parents%20are%20fleeing%20those%20walkable%20cities%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-with-young-kids-shun-big-cities-for-cheaper-areas-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etowns%20next%20door%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20the%20rise%20of%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20been%20a%20boon%20for%20care-strapped%20parents%2C%20but%20not%20so%20much%20for%20us%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-socializing-hard-work-from-home-return-to-office-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehumans%20who%20need%20socialization%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cheaper%20suburbs%20and%20exurbs%20make%20sense%20for%20cash-strapped%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20support%20is%20even%20beginning%20to%20factor%20into%20young%20people's%20decisions%20on%20whether%20to%20have%20a%20family%20at%20all.%20Over%20half%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%2047%25%20of%20millennials%20surveyed%20by%20Deloitte%20in%20late%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-afford-kids-family-living-paycheck-to-paycheck-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20expected%20starting%20a%20family%20to%20become%20harder%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20outright%20impossible.%20This%20hopelessness%20has%20reinforced%20the%20dissipation%20of%20the%20village.%20Since%20younger%20parents%20are%20now%20%26quot%3Bthe%20exception%20rather%20than%20the%20rule%2C%26quot%3B%20Twenge%20said%2C%20the%20share%20of%20people%20with%20peers%20going%20through%20the%20same%20stage%20of%20parenting%20has%20shrunk.%20Over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20the%20birth%20rate%20among%2040-%20to%2045-year-olds%20has%20slowly%20been%20ticking%20up%3B%20it's%20even%20more%20pronounced%20for%20those%20ages%2035%20to%2039.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20birth%20rates%20for%20those%20ages%2020%20to%2034%20have%20all%20fallen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fp2FhL%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Birth%20rates%20by%20age%20group%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Rep.%20Brittany%20Pettersen%20of%20Colorado%2C%20a%20Democratic%20millennial%20who%20has%20a%20young%20kid%2C%20was%20able%20to%20experience%20the%20type%20of%20village%20that%20is%20all%20too%20rare%20these%20days.%20When%20she%20visited%20a%20friend's%20house%2C%20the%20houses%20were%20clustered%20around%20a%20communal%20area%20with%20a%20playground%2C%20grass%2C%20and%20tables%20where%20kids%20could%20go%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20come%20out%20and%20bring%20their%20food%20out%20and%20help%20each%20other%20watch%20their%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20It%20was%20a%20simple%20reality%2C%20but%20one%20that%20showed%20the%20way%20that%20things%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20have%20to%20rethink%20the%20many%20ways%20in%20which%20we've%20made%20this%20much%20more%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Pettersen%20told%20me.%20Her%20generation%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20dealing%20with%20%26quot%3Bso%20many%20of%20the%20failed%20policies%26quot%3B%20that%20have%20led%20to%20a%20village%20like%20that%20feeling%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20are%20these%20physical%20villages%20so%20rare%3F%20Pettersen%20blames%20failed%20tax%20policies%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20continue%20to%20cut%20taxes%20for%20the%20most%20wealthy%20and%20we%20don't%20reinvest%20back%20in%20communities%20for%20the%20critical%20services%20to%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20for%20regular%20people%2C%20we%20just%20continue%20to%20see%20this%20opportunity%20gap%20increasing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20generations%20that%20are%20already%20spending%20less%20time%20with%20others%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20experiencing%20higher%20rates%20of%20depression%2C%20coupled%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cost-of-living-alcohol-coffee-going-out-more-expensive-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efun%20activities%20becoming%20increasingly%20financially%20out%20of%20reach%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20peer%20cohort%20of%20parents%20may%20be%20another%20social%20blow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20spending%20less%20time%20with%20people%20face%20to%20face%2C%20and%20that%20can%20be%20tough%20when%20you're%20entering%20parenthood%2C%26quot%3B%20Twenge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20ability%20to%20make%20a%20choice%2C%20and%20how%20to%20fix%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20speaking%20with%20parents%2C%20lawmakers%2C%20and%20experts%2C%20one%20thing%20became%20clear%20about%20the%20state%20of%20parenthood%20in%20America%3A%20It's%20becoming%20a%20decision%20that's%20turned%20from%20a%20normal%20progression%20of%20life%20into%20a%20thicket%20of%20difficult%20choices.%20Many%20are%20opting%20out%20of%20having%20kids%20altogether%2C%20creating%20a%20different%20type%20of%20void.%20Tumbling%20birth%20rates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-population-decline-worker-shortage-labor-birth-rates-immigration-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emight%20spell%20future%20economic%20disaster%20for%20America%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20also%20means%20those%20who%20are%20having%20kids%20are%20feeling%20more%20isolated%2C%20standing%20alone%20on%20a%20costly%2C%20shrinking%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20so%20financially%20impossible%26quot%3B%20to%20think%20about%20becoming%20a%20parent%2C%20Pettersen%20said.%20And%20yet%2C%20there%20she%20is.%20She's%20still%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20balance%20everything%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20we%20don't%20make%20it%20easy%20for%20parents%2C%20and%20we%20don't%20have%20that%20community%20support%20and%20those%20community%20connections%20previous%20generations%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20there%20aren't%20policy%20solutions%3A%20Rep.%20Becca%20Balint%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Vermont%2C%20didn't%20have%20her%20first%20kid%20until%20she%20was%20about%2039.%20She%20said%20policies%20like%20the%20child%20tax%20credit%20and%20lowering%20student-loan%20burdens%20%E2%80%94%20alongside%20investing%20in%20affordable%20housing%20and%20childcare%20%E2%80%94%20could%20help%20address%20some%20parental%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20those%20expenses%20that%20we%20are%20able%20to%20stabilize%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20young%20families%2C%20and%20it%20takes%20off%20that%20incredible%20stress%20and%20anxiety%20that%20you%20feel%2C%20and%20loneliness%20when%20you%20feel%20like%2C%20I'm%20working%20as%20hard%20as%20I%20can%20and%20I%20can't%20seem%20to%20get%20on%20top%20of%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Balint%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20used%20to%20be%20the%20case%2C%20Pettersen%20said%2C%20that%20each%20generation%20in%20America%20would%20have%20it%20better%20than%20the%20last.%20That's%20no%20longer%20true.%20Until%20the%201970s%2C%20it%20would%20take%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.piie.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Ffurman2021-07-29.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etypical%20American%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%2023%20years%20to%20double%20their%20incomes%20%E2%80%94%20once%20a%20generation.%20As%20of%202021%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faoc-rips-inequality-gap-for-doubling-income-grown-100-years-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etakes%20over%20100%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20economic%20struggles%20that%20come%20alongside%20it%2C%20Taylor%20has%20found%20parenthood%20to%20be%20transformative.%20He%20says%20it%20makes%20him%20think%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%20about%20what%20other%20people%20are%20going%20through%2C%20and%20to%20offer%20them%20more%20grace.%20Raising%20a%20young%20human%20is%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20love%20that%20sense%20of%20connectedness%20that%20I%20get%20with%20other%20parents%2C%20people%20I%20see%20in%20public%2C%20even%20if%20I%20don't%20know%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Taylor%20respects%20anyone%20who's%20decided%20that%20parenthood%20isn't%20for%20them.%20Broadly%2C%20he%20thinks%20our%20economic%20system%20is%20incompatible%20with%20giving%20people%20the%20true%20support%20they%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20desperately%20want%20to%20have%20a%20child%20or%20children%2C%20to%20raise%20a%20family%20%E2%80%94%20such%20an%20innate%20desire%20in%20so%20many%20people%20%E2%80%94%20you%20should%20have%20the%20chance%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20life%20should%20be%20such%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20have%20to%20count%20yourself%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjuliana-kaplan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJuliana%20Kaplan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20labor%20and%20inequality%20reporter%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-parents-struggle-lonely-childcare-costs-money-friends-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700392921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557698e4ca513d8242b3886%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-parents-struggle-lonely-childcare-costs-money-friends-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20the%20cost%20of%20raising%20a%20kid%20soaring%20and%20no%20%26quot%3Bvillage%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20them%2C%20millennial%20and%20Gen%20Z%20parents%20feel%20lonely%20and%20overwhelmed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-parents-struggle-lonely-childcare-costs-money-friends-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chhattisgarh%3A%20With%20No%20Common%20Wave%20in%20Sight%2C%20Congress%2C%20BJP%20Train%20Eyes%20on%20December%203%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19162810%2FF_H0xndXcAAdd-S.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatan%20(Chhattisgarh)%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ESeema%20Sahu%2C%20a%20small%20general%20store%20owner%20in%20Motipur%20village%20in%20Chhattisgarh%E2%80%99s%20Durg%20district%2C%20opened%20her%20shop%20earlier%20than%20usual%20on%20Friday.%20Her%20store%2C%20located%20on%20the%20road%20to%20Patan%2C%20chief%20minister%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%E2%80%99s%20home%20turf%2C%20is%20located%20right%20in%20front%20of%20the%20government%20school%20designated%20as%20the%20polling%20booth%20in%20their%20village.%20%E2%80%9CSince%20morning%2C%20Congress%20workers%20have%20been%20coming%20and%20buying%20various%20items%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sahu%20says%2C%20even%20as%20less%20than%20150%20metres%20away%2C%20steaming%20hot%20plates%20of%20fried%20fritters%20arrive%20on%20the%20table%20at%20a%20makeshift%20pandal%20where%20Congress%20agents%20are%20sitting.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Pramil%20Sahu%2C%20is%20Seema%E2%80%99s%20brother-in-law.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20sure%20of%20Baghel%20Kaka%E2%80%99s%20win.%20We%20are%20just%20trying%20to%20ensure%20that%20he%20wins%20with%20a%20huge%20margin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20311px)%2085vw%2C%20311px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22311%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-300x248.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-1024x845.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681756%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22257%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20Congress%20flags%20of%20all%20sizes%20dominate%20Kuruddih%2C%20Motipur%20and%20nearby%20Jheent%2C%20Tulsi%20village%2C%20in%20the%20same%20tehsil%2C%20flies%20flags%20of%20the%20Janta%20Congress%20Chhattisgarh%20(J)%20and%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20too.%20Near%20the%20polling%20booth%20in%20Tulsi%2C%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20agents%20are%20sitting%20across%20the%20main%20road.%20While%20the%20Congress%20workers%20have%20a%20steady%20input%20of%20fried%20fritters%2C%20the%20BJP%20is%20offering%20fruits%20to%20the%20voters%20coming%20to%20their%20pandal%20to%20check%20for%20their%20names.%20%E2%80%9CVijay%20Baghel%20is%20a%20worthy%20candidate%20who%20lived%20and%20worked%20among%20his%20people%20even%20after%20becoming%20an%20MP.%20We%20have%20full%20faith%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebhatija%3C%2Fem%3E%20(nephew)%20will%20win%20against%20Kaka%20(Kaka%20is%20an%20endearing%20term%20used%20for%20chief%20minister%20Bhupesh%20Baghel)%2C%E2%80%9D%20Anoop%20Sahu%2C%20a%20BJP%20worker%20from%20Tulsi%20village%2C%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20second%20phase%20of%20voting%20for%2070%20constituencies%20complete%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20fates%20of%20over%20a%20thousand%20candidates%20have%20been%20sealed%20in%20the%20electronic%20voting%20machines.%20While%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20the%20election%20held%20on%20November%207%20saw%20a%20weak%20voter%20turnout%2C%20the%20second%20phase%20of%20the%20election%20saw%20long%20queues%20in%20most%20polling%20booths.%20The%20voter%20turnout%20percentage%2C%20however%2C%20recorded%20a%20slight%20decrease%20from%202018%2C%20with%2075.08%25%20voter%20turnout.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChief%20minister%20Baghel%20stood%20in%20a%20line%20at%20his%20home%20village%20of%20Kuruddih%2C%20in%20Patan%20constituency%2C%20to%20cast%20a%20vote%20around%20noon.%20While%20speaking%20to%20the%20media%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20BJP%20is%20losing%2C%20we%20are%20coming%20back.%20The%20Congress%20party%20has%20fought%20the%20election%20on%20my%20face%3B%20still%20the%20party%20high%20command%20will%20decide%20who%20becomes%20the%20CM%20after%20we%20win.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20highest%20voter%20turnout%20was%20in%20Sanjari%20Balod%20constituency%20in%20Balod%20district%20with%2079.63%25%20and%20the%20lowest%20was%20recorded%20in%20Raipur%20(south)%20with%2052.11%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22At%20Tijara%2C%20Rajasthan's%20'Yogi'%20Talks%20of%20Rising%20Above%20Caste%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmahant-baba-balaknath-rajasthan-election-yogi-adityanath%5C%22%3EAt%20Tijara%2C%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Yogi%E2%80%99%20Talks%20of%20Rising%20Above%20Caste%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20villages%20in%20Bilaspur%20region%E2%80%99s%20Masturi%20constituency%20decided%20to%20boycott%20the%20election%20and%20even%20demonstrated%20in%20front%20of%20the%20district%20officials%20who%20had%20come%20to%20try%20and%20dissuade%20them%20from%20their%20boycott.%20According%20to%20the%20residents%2C%20the%20boycott%20was%20called%20after%20none%20of%20the%20political%20parties%20took%20seriously%20their%20complaints%20of%20not%20having%20a%20motorable%20road%20connecting%20them%20to%20the%20nearby%20regions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20fought%20the%20election%20on%20Baghel%E2%80%99s%20face%20and%20his%20tenure%20of%20five%20years%2C%20the%20BJP%20made%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20against%20Baghel.%20Both%20the%20parties%20tried%20to%20one-up%20the%20other%20in%20their%20manifestos%2C%20with%20the%20Congress%20declaring%20a%20scheme%20like%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Mahtari%20Vandan%20just%20days%20before%20the%20election.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20also%20pitched%20for%20Hindu%20votes%20by%20targeting%20conversions%20and%20inter-religious%20marriages%20across%20various%20districts%20in%20the%20plains.%20In%20Saja%20constituency%2C%20Bemetara%2C%20the%20BJP%20gave%20its%20ticket%20to%20Ishwar%20Sahu%2C%20father%20of%20Bhuneshwar%20Sahu%20who%20had%20died%20allegedly%20in%20a%20Hindu-Muslim%20clash%20in%202021%2C%20against%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20minister%20Ravindra%20Chaubey.%20The%20Congress%2C%20while%20not%20openly%20fighting%20for%20Hindu%20votes%2C%20had%20not%20shied%20away%20from%20adopting%20a%20soft%20Hindutva%20approach%20across%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20party%20had%20fielded%20Mahant%20Ram%20Sundar%20Das%20of%20the%20Doodhadhari%20Math%20against%20BJP%20leader%20and%20former%20minister%20Brijmohan%20Agarwal%20in%20Raipur%20(south)%2C%20a%20seat%20that%20many%20within%20the%20party%20believed%20was%20promised%20to%20mayor%20Dhebar.%20The%20fight%20over%20the%20seat%20turned%20dramatic%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20election%2C%20as%20Agarwal%20alleged%20the%20Congress%20had%20organised%20an%20attack%20on%20him%20while%20he%20was%20campaigning%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%2C%20however%2C%20might%20lose%20some%20votes%20from%20minority%20communities%20like%20the%20tribal%20or%20Christian%20voters%20to%20small%20parties%20like%20Hamar%20Raj%20and%20Sarv%20Adi%20Dal.%20One%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20for%20the%20Congress%20is%20also%20the%20Sahu%20community%2C%20one%20of%20the%20major%20OBC%20groups%2C%20who%20feel%20sidelined%20by%20the%20ruling%20government.%20The%20BJP%20has%20actively%20worked%20on%20gaining%20support%20from%20the%20Sahu%20community%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20election.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Modi%20Says%20Congress%20Failed%20To%20'Control%20Naxal%20Violence%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20Union%20Government%20Data%20Shows%20Otherwise%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpm-narendra-modi-congress-naxal-violence-union-government-data%5C%22%3EModi%20Says%20Congress%20Failed%20To%20%E2%80%98Control%20Naxal%20Violence%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20Union%20Government%20Data%20Shows%20Otherwise%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20political%20analysts%2C%20the%20elections%20in%20both%20phases%20across%20the%20state%20are%20unlike%20any%20held%20before%2C%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20common%20wave.%20%E2%80%9CIn%202018%2C%20it%20was%20an%20anti-incumbency%20wave%20and%20before%20that%2C%20Raman%20Singh%20was%20a%20strong%20factor.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20contest%20is%20between%20individual%20contestants%2C%20and%20each%20seat%20has%20its%20own%20dynamics%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20veteran%20political%20leader%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20BJP%20is%20confident%20of%20winning%2060%20seats%2C%20the%20Congress%20appears%20sure%20it%20will%20win%2075%20seats.%20However%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98war%20rooms%E2%80%99%20of%20both%20parties%20are%20struggling%20to%20get%20ground%20intelligence%20on%20the%20booth%20level.%20The%20results%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20will%20be%20declared%20on%20December%203.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700392533000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19162810%2FF_H0xndXcAAdd-S.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fchhattisgarh-with-no-common-wave-in-sight-congress-bjp-train-eyes-on-december-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20Congress%20fought%20the%20election%20on%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%E2%80%99s%20face%20and%20his%20tenure%20of%20five%20years%2C%20the%20BJP%20made%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20against%20Baghel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fchhattisgarh-with-no-common-wave-in-sight-congress-bjp-train-eyes-on-december-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20a%20Florida%20driver%20fed%20up%20with%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20created%20her%20own%20shuttle%20service%20so%20she%20could%20make%20more%20money%20and%20work%20fewer%20hours%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222989%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22port%20of%20miami%20with%20cruise%20ships%20docked%20in%20blue-green%20waters%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655636ee4ca513d8242a86fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222242%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESherry%20charges%20%2450%20a%20ride%20for%20her%20cruise%20shuttle%20service.%3Cp%3Episaphotography%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Gen%20Xer%20ridehailing%20driver%20said%20she's%20been%20making%20more%20per%20day%20with%20her%20freelance%20shuttle%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20works%20fewer%20hours%20and%20pulls%20in%20%2450%20a%20ride%20by%20finding%20clients%20on%20Facebook%20and%20word%20of%20mouth.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20comes%20after%20months%20of%20struggling%20to%20even%20earn%20%24100%20a%20day%20in%20eight%20hours%20for%20Uber%20and%20Lyft.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESherry%2C%2058%2C%20was%20driving%20upwards%20of%2075%20hours%20a%20week%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-full-time-gas-driving-tips-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Lyft%2C%20struggling%20to%20pull%20in%20%24200%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Florida%20driver%20said%20that%20when%20she%20started%20six%20years%20ago%20she%20was%20easily%20earning%20that%20much%20working%20six%20to%20eight%20hours%2C%20but%20has%20struggled%20to%20reach%20that%20goal%20more%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20make%20all%20your%20drivers%20mad%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20have%20any%20left%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sherry%2C%20who%20asked%20to%20just%20use%20her%20first%20name%20for%20fear%20of%20professional%20repercussions.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20people%20that%20I%20talk%20to%2C%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20it%20anymore%2C%20and%20they're%20trying%20to%20find%20other%20things%20to%20do%20on%20their%20own%20so%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20drive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she's%20trying%20something%20different.%20She%20launched%20a%20shuttle%20service%20that%20she%20advertises%20on%20Facebook%20and%20through%20word%20of%20mouth.%20She%20charges%20%2450%20to%20take%20people%20to%20and%20from%20the%20cruise%20terminal%20near%20her%20home%2C%20and%20she%20now%20works%20fewer%20hours%20and%20spends%20more%20time%20with%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody's%20trying%20to%20do%20their%20own%20thing%2C%20whether%20they're%20a%20social%20media%20influencer%20or%20starting%20their%20own%20car%20detailing%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BRecently%2C%20because%20of%20inflation%2C%20a%20lot%20more%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20drive%2C%20figuring%20even%20if%20I%20get%20an%20extra%20%24100%20a%20week%2C%20that's%20groceries%20or%20the%20electric%20bill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20right.%20Millions%20of%20Americans%20are%20looking%20to%20gig%20jobs%20like%20ridehailing%20apps%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-workers-millennials-and-gen-z-out-earn-older-workers-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egrocery%20delivery%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20digital%20freelancing%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20the%209-to-5%20office%20job.%20US%20gig%20workers%20are%20estimated%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgig-economy-trends-workers-delivery-ride-hailing-apps-uber-doordash-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20than%20doubled%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20But%20as%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-hours-surge-pricing-part-time-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E%20search%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-flex-app-jobs-wages-gig-work-full-time-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20stability%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20are%20struggling%20to%20put%20food%20on%20the%20table%20as%20their%20earnings%20fall%20and%20competition%20grows.%20This%20has%20led%20some%20to%20abandon%20gig%20work%20entirely%20or%20start%20their%20own%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrowing%20frustration%20with%20ridehailing%20gigs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESherry%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20seven%2C%20started%20driving%20in%202017%20while%20still%20working%20at%20a%20pharmacy.%20She%20transitioned%20to%20full-time%20driving%20in%202019%20after%20she%20reported%20feeling%20overworked%20and%20underpaid%20at%20her%20pharmacy%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20way%20I%20could%20create%20my%20own%20schedule%2C%20could%20go%20see%20my%20kids%20more%20when%20I%20wanted%2C%20and%20I%20could%20travel%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherry%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seemed%20to%20work%20out%20really%20well%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20years%20that%20I%20did%20it.%20I%20couldn't%20have%20been%20happier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPre-pandemic%2C%20she%20worked%2030%20to%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20Monday%20through%20Friday%2C%20and%20she%20said%20it%20was%20fairly%20easy%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20When%20the%20pandemic%20struck%2C%20she%20drove%20essential%20workers%20to%20and%20from%20work%2C%20and%20the%20platforms%20offered%20substantial%20bonuses%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noticed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-uber-drivers-make-hours-burnout-tipping-arizona-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompetition%20for%20rides%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20accelerating%2C%20though%2C%20and%20she%20started%20making%20less%20for%20her%20rides%20as%20the%20years%20progressed.%20She%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20she's%20needed%20to%20work%2012%20to%2014%20hours%20each%20day%20%E2%80%94%2018%20hours%20one%20day%20%E2%80%94%20to%20make%20a%20similar%20amount%20to%20what%20she%20would%20make%20in%20around%20half%20the%20time%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20this%20for%20the%20freedom%20to%20set%20my%20own%20schedule%2C%20but%20it's%20coming%20at%20a%20price%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherry%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20even%20have%20freedom%20anymore%20because%20now%20I%20have%20to%20drive%20so%20much%2C%20I%20basically%20don't%20have%20a%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20she%20had%20a%20gross%20payment%20of%20over%20%2498%2C000%20from%20Uber%20for%20nearly%204%2C000%20completed%20trips%2C%20though%20her%20net%20payout%20was%20only%20%2455%2C000%20after%20fees%2C%20expenses%2C%20and%20taxes.%20This%20year%2C%20her%20net%20payout%20for%20the%20first%2010%20months%20of%20the%20year%20is%20around%20%2428%2C500%20for%20nearly%202%2C000%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESherry%20said%20she%20struggled%20to%20pay%20her%20bills%20as%20rides%20dry%20up.%20Some%20days%20recently%2C%20she%20would%20only%20make%20%24100%20in%20seven%20or%20eight%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20or%20about%20minimum%20wage%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20body%20takes%20a%20huge%20toll.%20It's%20just%20terrible%20sitting%20in%20the%20car%20all%20day%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherry%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20muscles%20are%20becoming%20weak%2C%20and%20I'm%20gaining%20weight%20because%20I'm%20not%20getting%20out%20and%20walking%20around.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20there%20would%20only%20be%20six%20or%20seven%20drivers%20waiting%20at%20the%20airport%20at%20a%20time%20for%20rides%2C%20but%20now%20there's%20over%2040.%20One%20day%2C%20she%20recalled%20220%20cars%20waiting%20when%20there%20were%20only%2040%20flights%20coming%20in%20that%20day.%20Some%20days%2C%20she%20waited%20nearly%20two%20hours%20for%20an%20airport%20trip%2C%20only%20for%20it%20to%20pay%20%247.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAirport%20trips%20used%20to%20be%20my%20bread%20and%20butter%2C%20but%20now%20it's%20all%20just%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20Sherry%20was%20offered%20a%20Lyft%20ride%20for%20%2450.69%20that%20was%20almost%20two%20hours%20and%20115%20miles.%20While%20she%20would%20make%20around%20%2425%20an%20hour%20for%20the%20trip%20itself%2C%20the%20amount%20she'd%20pay%20in%20gas%20there%20and%20back%20would%20amount%20to%20just%20%247%20an%20hour%20for%20the%20four-hour%20round%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20earnings%2C%20coupled%20with%20rising%20car%20maintenance%20costs%2C%20have%20led%20her%20to%20search%20for%20other%20work.%20She%20said%20the%20price%20for%20a%20set%20of%20tires%20doubled%20from%20%24400%20to%20%24850%20in%20her%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeing%20her%20own%20boss%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20on%20a%20cruise%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20Sherry%20said%20she%20heard%20passengers%20complain%20about%20how%20they%20couldn't%20find%20a%20shuttle%20to%20and%20from%20the%20cruise%20port.%20So%20last%20month%2C%20Sherry%20decided%20to%20supplement%20her%20income%20from%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20by%20starting%20a%20freelance%20shuttle%20service%2C%20an%20extension%20of%20some%20freelance%20airport%20trips%20she%20did%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20used%20to%20tip%20pretty%20good%2C%20but%20now%2C%20it's%20few%20and%20far%20between%20if%20you%20actually%20get%20a%20tip%20anymore.%20I'm%20better%20off%20doing%20my%20own%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20created%20a%20digital%20business%20card%20for%20her%20shuttle%20business%20and%20posted%20in%20Facebook%20groups%20offering%20her%20services.%20When%20she%20heard%20about%20the%20prices%20ridehailing%20companies%20were%20charging%20to%20get%20to%20the%20cruise%20ports%20%E2%80%94%20some%20charged%20upwards%20of%20%2490%20one%20way%20%E2%80%94%20she%20decided%20to%20charge%20%2450%20each%20way.%20She%20could%20pocket%20all%20%2450%2C%20whereas%20a%20comparable%20Uber%20ride%20she%20said%20would%20only%20give%20her%20%2430.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20made%20between%20%241%2C500%20and%20%241%2C700%20a%20week%20doing%20shuttle%20driving%20alongside%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20rides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20many%20Facebook%20groups%20ban%20advertisers%2C%20she's%20had%20some%20luck%20responding%20to%20comments%20for%20people%20looking%20for%20rides.%20Some%20days%2C%20she's%20making%20%24500%20working%20fewer%20hours%20than%20she%20would%20for%20%24200%20with%20Uber%20and%20Lyft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20clientele%20I%20have%20is%20different%20too%20because%20I'm%20driving%20tourists%2C%20and%20they're%20more%20apt%20to%20tip%2C%26quot%3B%20Sherry%20said.%20%26qu