e%20is%20off%20the%20table.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fworld%2Fstory%2Fus-house-passes-143-billion-in-military-aid-for-israel-despite-joe-biden-veto-threat-2457419-2023-11-03%5C%22%3Ehas%20proposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2414.3%20billion%20in%20fresh%20military%20aid%20to%20Israel%2C%20too%2C%20presumably%20to%20ensure%20that%20only%20his%20government%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%20some%20other%20country%20keen%20to%20fish%20in%20muddied%20waters%20%E2%80%93%20gets%20to%20supply%20all%20those%20less-than-lethal%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20doing%20the%20heroic%20things%20he%20is%20doing.%20Olaf%20Scholtz%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Esocialist%3C%2Fem%3E%20German%20chancellor%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Ffeatures%2F2023%2F10%2F26%2Fcomplete-censorship-germanys-palestinian-diaspora-fights-crackdown%5C%22%3Ehas%20outlawed%3C%2Fa%3E%20public%20demonstrations%20in%20support%20of%20Palestine%20in%20his%20country%20because%20permitting%20pro-Palestine%20marches%20would%20be%20anti-Semitic.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-politics-67432393%5C%22%3EKeir%20Starmer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20British%20Labour%20Party%2C%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20agree%20more.%20For%20Starmer%2C%20all%20talk%20of%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20Gaza%20is%20pure%20sacrilege.%20(Indeed%2C%20Jeremy%20Corbyn%2C%20Starmer%E2%80%99s%20predecessor%2C%20had%20lost%20his%20leadership%20position%20precisely%20because%20he%20had%20committed%20a%20grievous%20error%3A%20he%20used%20to%20believe%20one%20could%20question%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20%3Cem%3Eand%20yet%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20a%20liberal.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20be%20reasonably%20certain%20that%20had%20the%20great%20(Jewish-born)%20historian%20Eric%20Hobsbawm%20been%20around%20today%2C%20he%20would%20have%20been%20pilloried%20as%20a%20vile%20anti-Semite%3A%20aside%20from%20referring%20to%20Tony%20Blair%2C%20Keir%20Starmer%E2%80%99s%20moral-intellectual%20progenitor%2C%20as%20%E2%80%98%E2%80%99(Margaret)%20Thatcher%20in%20trousers%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20never%20managed%20to%20find%20flattering%20things%20to%20say%20about%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20are%20concerned%20here%20not%20with%20heretics%20like%20Hobsbawm%20but%20true-blue%20liberals%20like%20Biden%20and%20Starmer%20and%20Scholtz.%20The%20liberal%20dilemma%20over%20Palestine%20inheres%20in%20a%20shocked%20surprise%20that%20Palestinians%20fail%20to%20grasp%20a%20truism%3A%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20Western%20liberal%20who%20knows%20best%20what%E2%80%99s%20best%20for%20Palestine.%20This%20dilemma%20was%20brought%20home%20to%20me%20with%20startling%20clarity%20a%20few%20days%20ago%20by%20a%20video%20featuring%20a%20conversation%20between%20the%20Egyptian-American%20comedian%20Bassem%20Youssef%20and%20the%20British%20TV%20talk-show%20host%20Piers%20Morgan%20around%20the%20ongoing%20Gaza%20war.%20This%20conversation%20really%C2%A0%20followed%20upon%20an%20earlier%20TV%20programme%20where%20Morgan%20in%20London%20spoke%20with%20Youssef%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20about%20the%20crisis%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20course%20of%20that%20interview%2C%20Youssef%20had%20spoken%20witheringly%20about%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20studied%20ambivalence%20on%20the%20Palestine%20question%2C%20ambivalence%20that%20was%20often%20indistinguishable%20from%20moral%20equivocation.%20The%20great%20Western%20democracies%2C%20he%20implied%2C%20were%20unwilling%20or%20unable%2C%20or%20both%2C%20to%20comprehend%20the%20horrendous%20inequities%20Palestinians%20were%20obliged%20to%20suffer%20daily%20at%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMorgan%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20clearly%20felt%20frustrated%20by%20his%20inability%20to%20draw%20Youssef%20into%20an%20excoriation%20of%20what%20Hamas%20stood%20for.%20Perplexed%20by%20Youssef%E2%80%99s%20apparent%20intransigence%2C%20Morgan%20flew%20all%20the%20way%20to%20LA%20a%20few%20days%20later%20and%20